#: src/graphics-windowing.md:3
msgid "Drivers"
msgstr ""

#: src/graphics-windowing.md:5
msgid "VESA (vesad)"
msgstr ""

#: src/graphics-windowing.md:7
msgid ""
"vesad is not really a driver, it writes to a framebuffer given by firmware "
"(via UEFI or BIOS software interrupts)."
msgstr ""

#: src/graphics-windowing.md:9
msgid ""
"Because we don't have GPU drivers yet, we rely on what firmware gives to us."
msgstr ""

#: src/graphics-windowing.md:11
msgid "GPUs"
msgstr ""

#: src/graphics-windowing.md:13
msgid ""
"On Linux/BSDs, the GPU communication with the kernel is done by the DRM "
"system (Direct Rendering Manager, `libdrm` library), that Mesa3D drivers use "
"to work (Mesa3D implement OpenGL/Vulkan drivers, DRM expose the hardware "
"interfaces)."
msgstr ""

#: src/graphics-windowing.md:15
msgid ""
"Said this, in Redox a \"DRM driver\" needs to be an user-space driver which "
"use the system calls/schemes to communicate with the hardware."
msgstr ""

#: src/graphics-windowing.md:17
msgid ""
"The last step is to implement the Redox backend in our Mesa3D [fork](https://"
"gitlab.redox-os.org/redox-os/mesa)/[recipe](https://gitlab.redox-os.org/"
"redox-os/cookbook/-/blob/master/recipes/mesa/recipe.toml) to use these user-"
"space drivers."
msgstr ""

#: src/graphics-windowing.md:19
msgid "Software Rendering"
msgstr ""

#: src/graphics-windowing.md:21
msgid ""
"We don't have GPU drivers yet but [LLVMpipe](https://docs.mesa3d.org/drivers/"
"llvmpipe.html) (OpenGL CPU emulation) is working."
msgstr ""

#: src/graphics-windowing.md:23
msgid "Orbital"
msgstr ""

#: src/graphics-windowing.md:25
msgid ""
"The Orbital desktop environment provides a display server, window manager "
"and compositor."
msgstr ""

#: src/graphics-windowing.md:27
msgid "Comparison with X11/Wayland"
msgstr ""

#: src/graphics-windowing.md:29
msgid ""
"This display server is more simple than X11 and Wayland making the porting "
"task more quick and easy, it's not advanced like X11 and Wayland yet but "
"enough to port most Linux/BSD programs."
msgstr ""

#: src/graphics-windowing.md:31
msgid ""
"Compared to Wayland, Orbital has one server implementation, while Wayland "
"provide protocols for compositors."
msgstr ""

