#: src/graphics-windowing.md:72
msgid "Porting"
msgstr ""

#: src/graphics-windowing.md:74
msgid "If you want to port a program to Orbital, see below:"
msgstr ""

#: src/graphics-windowing.md:76
msgid ""
"If the program is written in Rust probably it works on Orbital because the "
"`winit` crate is used in most places, but there are programs that access X11 "
"or Wayland directly. You need to port these programs to `winit` and merge on "
"upstream."
msgstr ""

#: src/graphics-windowing.md:78
msgid ""
"If the program is written in C or C++ and access X11 or Wayland directly, it "
"must be ported to the [Orbital library](https://gitlab.redox-os.org/redox-os/"
"liborbital)."
msgstr ""
